The reason for the IAE is as follows:

StyledText.modifyContent(Event, boolean) calls content.replaceTextRange(...)
which can cause other modifications. These modifications get correctly reported
to the widget via textChangeListener. The problem is that after calling
content.replaceTextRange(...) it tries to restore the selection (and caret)
using outdated values from the initial event passed into modifyContent.

